        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I am not sure this is worth the effort, but it seems worthy enough to consider.\n\nShahar and I were chatting about preventing access to unit tests by web servers, in order to minimize unforseen security risks.\n\nFor example, we could test for something like $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'] or add a \".htaccess\" file to help prevent accidentally executing files in the \"tests\" directory."
        },
